      <section eId="sec_2126">
        <num>2126</num>
        <heading>Powers of commissioner</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_2126__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The commissioner shall prescribe\nand provide suitable forms of applications, certificates of title,\nnotices of security interests, and all other notices and forms necessary\nto carry out the provisions of this article.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_2126__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The commissioner may:\n</p>
          </content>
          <paragraph eId="sec_2126__subsec_b__subsec_1">
            <num>(1)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Make necessary investigations to procure information required to\ncarry out the provisions of this article; and\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_2126__subsec_b__subsec_2">
            <num>(2)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Adopt and enforce reasonable rules and regulations to carry out\nthe provisions of this article; and\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
          <paragraph eId="sec_2126__subsec_b__subsec_3">
            <num>(3)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Upon assigning a new identifying number to a vehicle if it has\nnone, or its identifying number is destroyed or obliterated, shall\neither issue a new certificate of title showing the new identifying\nnumber or make an appropriate indorsement on the original certificate.\n</p>
            </content>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
      </section>
